<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 06 at 5:58PM MDT until July 06 at 10:00PM MDT by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 615 PM MDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN PHILLIPS COUNTY...
At 558 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 13 miles north of Fourchette to 14 miles east of
Zortman, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
These severe thunderstorms will remain over mainly rural areas of
southwestern Phillips County.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
